          "triggerring_time": 1.5,
          "source_object_fileID": 665489382,
          "condition": "Scene object 'ScoreManager' is a PrefabInstance (source guid: b547ef9648ba13749828322159356dee) with runtime refs set via m_Modifications: ScoreText(fileID: 1410783274), AmountUI(fileID: 101471811), Timer(fileID: 1937840742), winlosescript(fileID: 283832888), winAmount=4. MonoBehaviour script guid f7de224e5fee443418417f9f2bfa2998 (Scoremanager.cs) initializes AmountUI.text in Start() and updates Timer text in Update(). The only public method is changescore(int), which requires a parameter and cannot be invoked by this framework’s Trigger action (only supports public no-arg methods). The ScoreManager object also has no Collider/Rigidbody/EventTrigger, so it cannot be directly interacted with under the Trigger action constraints. Therefore, to validate the conditional event that Scoremanager would invoke when score == winAmount, we directly trigger the downstream no-arg method WinLose.Winlevel() on the referenced winlosescript (component fileID: 283832888). Expected: This simulates the event that Scoremanager would call upon reaching the target score; in parallel, during the 1.5s wait, Update() should be running and updating the Timer text (Time.time formatted as 0.0).",
          "triggerring_events": [
            {
